    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-02T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="50"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d50">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Prime Minister <persName type="from">Churchill</persName> to
                        President <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d50fn1">Sent to Washington by the United States Military
                        Attaché, London, via Army channels; forwarded by the White House Map Room to
                        Roosevelt, who was at Hyde Park, as telegram No. <gloss target="#t_Red1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Red</hi>
                        </gloss> 355.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-02">2 September
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Prime Minister to President Roosevelt. Personal and top secret. Number 778.</p>
                <p>I am delighted that Eleanor will come.</p>
                <p>The doctors are resolute that I can go bar a setback. I cannot reach <gloss
                        target="#t_Octagon1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Octagon</hi>
                    </gloss> till noon 11th.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
